&gt; Sounds like your pgcc compiler installation is busted.  You&#39;ll need to get that fixed to compile/install Open MPI.<br>
<br>
An alternative might be to use a system compiler (which is probably gcc or<br>
clang) for C and C++ and only use pgfortran for the Fortran parts of OpenMPI,<br>
i.e. try something like<br>
<br>
./configure CC=gcc CXX=g++ FC=pgf90 F77=pgf77 F90=pgf90<br>
--prefix=/opt/openmpi-1.8.5_pgf90<br>
<br>
Regards, Thomas Jahns<br>
